main event: A radar operator and a pilot observed an unidentified object on radar and visually on 30 October 1952.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 5-6 minutes.,The object was moving much faster than the aircraft.,The object was at a greater altitude than the aircraft.,The object's maneuvers were inconsistent with known aircraft.,The conclusion drawn was unknown with no explanation.
location: 122-23 24°45'N (1°02' E of OCEAN), Unknown Region, Unknown Country
witness description: radar operator and pilot of the aircraft
